Stryker Corporation (SYK) Shares Sold by Tokio Marine Asset Management Co. Ltd.

Posted by Dan Jones on Jul 23rd, 2017 // No Comments 

Tokio Marine Asset Management Co. Ltd. lowered its position in shares of Stryker Corporation (NYSE:SYK) by 24.5% during the first quarter, according to its most recent filing with the SEC. The fund owned 4,791 shares of the medical technology company’s stock after selling 1,554 shares during the period. Tokio Marine Asset Management Co. Ltd.’s holdings in Stryker Corporation were worth $631,000 as of its most recent SEC filing. 
Several other hedge funds have also recently added to or reduced their stakes in SYK. DZ BANK AG Deutsche Zentral Genossenschafts Bank Frankfurt am Main purchased a new stake in Stryker Corporation during the fourth quarter worth about $7,539,000. Barings LLC boosted its stake in Stryker Corporation by 220.4% in the fourth quarter. Barings LLC now owns 13,839 shares of the medical technology company’s stock worth $1,658,000 after buying an additional 9,520 shares in the last quarter. Arrowstreet Capital Limited Partnership purchased a new stake in Stryker Corporation during the fourth quarter worth about $48,221,000. CAMG Solamere Management LLC purchased a new stake in Stryker Corporation during the fourth quarter worth about $968,000. Finally, Cypress Wealth Advisors LLC purchased a new stake in Stryker Corporation during the fourth quarter worth about $202,000. Institutional investors and hedge funds own 74.25% of the company’s stock. 




Shares of Stryker Corporation (NYSE:SYK) traded down 0.82% during trading on Friday, hitting $146.19. The stock had a trading volume of 1,158,620 shares. The stock has a market capitalization of $54.64 billion, a price-to-earnings ratio of 32.85 and a beta of 0.79. Stryker Corporation has a one year low of $106.48 and a one year high of $148.15. The stock has a 50 day moving average price of $142.05 and a 200-day moving average price of $132.85. 


 Get Stryker Corporation alerts:



Stryker Corporation (NYSE:SYK) last released its quarterly earnings data on Tuesday, April 25th. The medical technology company reported $1.48 earnings per share for the quarter, beating the Thomson Reuters’ consensus estimate of $1.43 by $0.05. Stryker Corporation had a return on equity of 24.26% and a net margin of 14.33%. The company had revenue of $2.96 billion for the quarter, compared to the consensus estimate of $2.90 billion. During the same quarter last year, the business posted $1.24 EPS. Stryker Corporation’s revenue for the quarter was up 18.4% on a year-over-year basis. On average, equities research analysts predict that Stryker Corporation will post $6.43 earnings per share for the current year. 
The company also recently disclosed a quarterly dividend, which will be paid on Monday, July 31st. Investors of record on Friday, June 30th will be issued a dividend of $0.425 per share. This represents a $1.70 annualized dividend and a dividend yield of 1.16%. The ex-dividend date is Wednesday, June 28th. Stryker Corporation’s dividend payout ratio (DPR) is 38.20%. 
TRADEMARK VIOLATION NOTICE: “Stryker Corporation (SYK) Shares Sold by Tokio Marine Asset Management Co. Ltd.” was published by BNB Daily and is the property of of BNB Daily. If you are accessing this report on another site, it was illegally copied and republished in violation of US and international trademark and copyright laws. The original version of this report can be accessed at https://www.baseball-news-blog.com/2017/07/23/tokio-marine-asset-management-co-ltd-has-631000-position-in-stryker-corporation-syk-updated-updated.html. 
A number of research firms have recently issued reports on SYK. Zacks Investment Research upgraded Stryker Corporation from a “hold” rating to a “buy” rating and set a $163.00 price objective on the stock in a research report on Monday, July 17th. Citigroup Inc. boosted their price target on Stryker Corporation from $114.00 to $125.00 and gave the company a “sell” rating in a research note on Friday, June 9th. Oppenheimer Holdings, Inc. reaffirmed a “hold” rating on shares of Stryker Corporation in a research note on Monday, June 19th. BidaskClub lowered Stryker Corporation from a “strong-buy” rating to a “buy” rating in a research note on Tuesday, June 13th. Finally, Morgan Stanley boosted their price target on Stryker Corporation from $145.00 to $155.00 and gave the company an “overweight” rating in a research note on Wednesday, June 21st. Three research analysts have rated the stock with a sell rating, seven have given a hold rating and thirteen have issued a buy rating to the stock. The company presently has an average rating of “Hold” and a consensus target price of $139.08.
In other Stryker Corporation news, insider Timothy J. Scannell sold 13,322 shares of Stryker Corporation stock in a transaction dated Tuesday, May 2nd. The stock was sold at an average price of $135.89, for a total transaction of $1,810,326.58. The sale was disclosed in a filing with the SEC, which is available through this hyperlink. Also, insider David Floyd sold 19,305 shares of Stryker Corporation stock in a transaction dated Wednesday, July 12th. The stock was sold at an average price of $144.56, for a total value of $2,790,730.80. The disclosure for this sale can be found here. In the last three months, insiders have sold 40,008 shares of company stock worth $5,669,088. 7.40% of the stock is currently owned by company insiders. 
Stryker Corporation Company Profile
Stryker Corporation is a medical technology company. The Company offers a range of medical technologies, including orthopedic, medical and surgical, and neurotechnology and spine products. The Company’s segments include Orthopaedics; MedSurg; Neurotechnology and Spine, and Corporate and Other. The Orthopaedics segment includes reconstructive (hip and knee) and trauma implant systems and other related products. 

 
